verbose_text: Different content free SA (1.0, 2.0 and 4.0 mg.mL -1) was used to block E-selectin receptor beforehand, and the results showed that the uptake of SA-PEG-DXM micelles in LPS activated HUVECs gradually diminished with the increased doses of free SA.
evidence: SA (1.0, 2.0 and 4.0 mg.mL -1 ) was used to block E-selectin receptor
